used in financing activities was $7.0 billion in 2015, $10.9 billion lower than
2014. dividend payments on common shares increased to $2.88 per share from
$2.70 per share and totaled $12.1 billion, a pay-out of 75 percent of net
income. during the first quarter of 2015, the corporation issued $8.0 billion
of long-term debt. total debt increased $9.6 billion to $38.7 billion at yearend.
exxonmobil
